sequenceDiagram
    autonumber
    participant TM  as Poll Timer
    participant C   as C Binary (der_poll)
    participant SRV as 2030.5 Server
    participant SCH as Local Scheduler
    participant PY  as Python Gateway

    Note over TM,C: steady state — poll timer fires

    TM  ->> C: RESOURCE_POLL (FunctionSetAssignmentsList, poll_rate=10s)
    C   ->> SRV: GET /edev/{sfdi}/fsa
    SRV -->> C: 200 OK  FunctionSetAssignments (unchanged)
    Note over C: no change — discard, reschedule timer

    TM  ->> C: RESOURCE_POLL (DERProgramList, poll_rate=10s)
    C   ->> SRV: GET /edev/{sfdi}/fsa/derp
    SRV -->> C: 200 OK  DERProgramList (unchanged)
    Note over C: no change — discard, reschedule timer

    Note over TM,SRV: server updates a DERControl

    TM  ->> C: RESOURCE_POLL (DERControlList, poll_rate=10s)
    C   ->> SRV: GET /edev/{sfdi}/fsa/derp/{id}/derc
    SRV -->> C: 200 OK  DERControlList (new or changed control)

    Note over C: RESOURCE_UPDATE — model changed

    C   ->> SCH: update_resource() → rebuild dependency graph
    SCH ->> SCH: reschedule events with updated DERControlList

    Note over SCH: SCHEDULE_UPDATE

    SCH ->> C: update_schedule(s)

    alt new control becomes active now
        C   ->> PY: EVENT_JSON: {type:start, mrid:..., control:{...}}
        Note over PY: bridge.apply() → write Modbus registers
    else active control superseded or cancelled
        C   ->> PY: EVENT_JSON: {type:end, mrid:...}
        Note over PY: bridge._relinquish() → write 0 to tracked registers
    else no active controls remain and DefaultDERControl exists
        C   ->> PY: EVENT_JSON: {type:default_control, control:{...}}
        Note over PY: bridge.apply() → apply fallback setpoints
    end
